  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nA clear and concise description of what the bug is.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Run `git clone https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism-tutorial.git && cd optimism-tutorial`\r\n1. Don't add `require('@eth-optimism/hardhat-ovm')`\r\n1. Run `yarn && yarn add @eth-optimism/hardhat-ovm`\r\n1. Run `yarn hardhat compile --network optimism`\r\n1. Run `yarn hardhat test --network optimism`\r\n1. See the following error:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"861\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-04-21 at 10 54 24 AM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37757724/115599038-b5977080-a2a0-11eb-88ee-275e425d1e51.png\">\r\n\r\n(I truncated the data field of the image above because it's long)\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n**_This issue is for reference._**\r\n\r\n[After a discussion in discord](https://discord.com/channels/667044843901681675/832331828072939530/834434959698952222) this issue was found to be due to excluding the `hardhat-ovm` plugin from one's hardhat config file, step 2 in the \"Steps to Reproduce\" above.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this issue is to document a real world user's experience from working through our [`optimism-tutorial`](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism-tutorial)'s README. Documentation should be clear enough that should _not_ be skipping steps and be easy enough so that someone with minimal experience could follow along.",
